nagement and budget previously she served as deputy united states trade representative from  to  contents  career  board of directors member  personal information  references  external links careeredit prior to becoming deputy trade representative she had served since  as president and ceo of the university system of maryland foundation from  to  she served as dean of the school of public policy at the university of maryland college park where she remains on the faculty earlier in her career she served as an aide to thenus senator john danforth as a foreign service officer in the state department as a wellrespected directorgeneral of the foreign and commercial service within the us department of commerce and as a business development executive at motorola her first job was a trade negotiator with the ustr office and she later served as trade policy officer in the us embassy in tokyo she negotiated the united statescanada softwood lumber dispute by signing a deal along with canadian trade minister david emerson on september   that gave canada  out of the  billion dollars that the country lost in the dispute on january   as the bush administration neared its end schwab reportedly announced retaliatory tariffs on dozens of european luxury items including french truffles irish oatmeal italian sparkling water and roquefort cheese the european ban on us beef containing hormones was the reason cited by the us for the retaliatory action roquefort cheese made from sheeps milk in a region of southern france was hit with a  tariff apparently the highest level by far of any in the package when a  tariff was placed on the cheese in  the report says josé bové helped marshal opposition as of  the french complaint with the roquefort tariff is being pursued through diplomatic channels she helped to launch negotiations for acta board of directors memberedit on june   the board of directors of fedex corporation elected ambassador schwab as a director the board also appointed ambassador schwab as a member of its compensation committee she also sits on the board of directors at boeing and caterpillar inc personal informationedit schwab is a resident of annapolis maryland she attended williams college ba in political economy stanford university ma in development policy and george washington university phd in public administration and international business she is a  graduate of international school bangkok on november   schwabs husband curtis carroll diedcitation needed referencesedit  susan schwab professor university of maryland school of public policy archived from the original on may   retrieved    emerson and us counterpart ink softwood deal archived from the original on  retrieved    bush war on roquefort raises a stink in france departing officials set duty at  by edward cody the washington post  p a retrieved   proposed us acta plurilateral intellectual property trade agreement  retrieved  from google cache external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to susan schwab political offices preceded by rob portman united states trade representative – succeeded by ron kirk v t e boeing companies boeing aircraft holding company boeing australia boeing canada boeing capital boeing commercial airplanes boeing defense space  security boeing phantom works boeing rotorcraft systems boeing uk hrl laboratories jeppesen mcdonnell douglas narus spectrolab united launch alliance people william m allen james a bell john h biggs william boeing john bryson arthur d collins jr philip m condit william m daley darleen druyun kenneth duberstein edgar gott philip g johnson john mcdonnell james mcnerney susan schwab michael m sears frank shrontz harry stonecipher malcolm t stamper thornton wilson mike s zafirovski projects bct modernization boeing black boeing x series boeing hydrofoils boeing jetfoils connexion by boeing future combat systems facilities boeing everett factory boeing plant  boeing plant  boeing renton factory boeing south carolina boeing st