s trade policy initiatives including landmark trade legislation that congress enacted in  and   previously schwab served as a trade policy officer in the us embassy in tokyo her first job was as an agricultural trade negotiator at ustr ambassador schwab is a member of the council on foreign relations the aspen strategy group a fellow of the national academy of public administration  napa  and a trustee of the conference board she is the author of tradeoffs negotiating the omnibus trade act harvard business school press  as well as articles on usjapan trade relations trade politics and public policy education she serves on the boards of boeing caterpillar fedex and marriottshe holds a ba from williams college a master’s from stanford university and a phd from the george washington university  admissions why marylandschedule a visitapply nowba degreempp degreephd program centers do good institutecenter for global sustainabilitycenter for international and security studies at maryland cissmcenter for public policy  private enterprise cpppenational center for smart growth researchsafe center newsroom feature storiespress releasesin the newseventsthe policy exchangeget spp news connect with us university of maryland school of public policy  van munching hall college park md  • phone  • fax  leave this field blank cms login susan schwab  school of public policy skip to main content search form search newsroomfacultyresearchgiving about the schoolwhy marylandundergraduate programsgraduate programsexecutive programsresearch  centersleadershipmeet our facultymeet our staffnewsroomspotlightsfaculty  staff openingsdirections and parkingcontact usundergraduateabout usacademicsadmissionsstudent engagementgraduateexecutive educationabout usleadership and management programsleadership development workshopsexecutive coaching group facilitation and program managementpartners and programsfederal acquisitions managementpublic policy programsunderstanding public policy and legislationp